    "Figure 4b illustrates the overall architecture of hierarchical pooling.",
    "In Fig. 4b, the hierarchical architecture consists of three separate modules, each containing a convolutional layer and a pooling layer.",
    "The output of each block is summarized by a readout function to generate a fixed-size feature representation.",
    "Ultimately, these independent representations are concatenated and fed into the MLP to perform the downstream tasks.",
    "According to the different ways of constructing the coarsening graph, hierarchical pooling methods can be divided into node clustering, node sampling, and other pooling methods."
